    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Inspection - Flywheel Housing Bore Concentricity
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Flywheel Housing Bore Concentricity</title>
        <figure id="f2651317" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Flywheel housing bore concentricity</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to the crankshaft. Place the tip of the dial indicator against the
                flywheel housing bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slowly rotate the crankshaft. Record the total indicator variation and compare the result to
                the flywheel housing bore concentricity specification.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
